# Privacy Policy for Pocketful

Last Updated: April 28, 2026

## Introduction

Welcome to Pocketful!

Pocketful, also known in Chinese as 鸦鸦盒子, is a creative journaling and collection app. In this Privacy Policy, we refer to Pocketful as “the App”.

We respect your privacy and designed the App so that your creative content stays on your device. We do not run our own backend server for the App, do not require you to create an account, and do not collect, store, or sell your personal data on our servers.

This Privacy Policy explains what information is stored locally on your device, which permissions the App may request, and what happens when you delete the App.

## Information We Collect

We do not collect personal data on our servers.

The App does not use Firebase Analytics, Supabase, or any other analytics or tracking SDK. We do not operate a cloud database for your content, and we do not have access to what you create inside the App.

## Content Stored on Your Device

When you use the App, the following content may be stored locally on your device only:

- Photos and images you capture or import
- Audio recordings you create
- Text notes and written content
- Drawings and doodles
- Cards and collections, including tin boxes you create

This content does not leave your device unless you choose to share or export it yourself, for example through iOS system sharing. We do not upload your creative content to our servers.

## Device Permissions

The App may request certain system permissions only when needed:

- Camera – to take photos you choose to use in your cards or stickers
- Photo Library – to import existing photos or images
- Microphone – to record audio that you choose to add

These permissions are used only to support the features you choose to use inside the App. We do not use these permissions to collect data on our servers. You can change these permissions at any time in your device settings, but some features may not work without them.

## Data Storage and Deletion

All of your creative content is stored locally on your device. The App does not currently provide cloud backup or account sync.

If you delete the App, all data stored inside the App will be deleted from your device and cannot be recovered by us.

If you want to keep your creations, please save or export them before deleting the App.

## Data Sharing

Because we do not collect your personal data on our servers:

- We do not sell your data
- We do not share your creative content with third parties
- We do not use your photos, audio, text, drawings, cards, or collections for any other purpose

Your content only leaves your device when you choose to share or export it, for example by sending an image or card to a friend through the iOS share sheet.

## Children’s Privacy

The App is designed to be gentle and privacy-friendly. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children on our servers, because we do not collect personal data on our servers at all.

Parents or guardians can manage app access and permissions through the device’s system settings and parental controls.

## Your Rights and Control

Because your content is stored locally on your device, you control your information directly:

- You can view and manage your content inside the App
- You can delete individual creations at any time
- You can delete all locally stored App data by deleting the App from your device

If you live in a region with specific privacy laws, such as the EU or California, and have questions, you can contact us using the email below. In most cases, the answer will be that your content is stored only on your device and is not accessible to us.

## Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make changes, we will update the “Last Updated” date at the top of this document.

Substantial changes may also be highlighted in the App.

